{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17595971","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17595971"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:08:55+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:08:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15386"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15386","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15386"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.38,0.25,0.08,0.04,0.25]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8077"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69836"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8077","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8077"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15386"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55292"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19603"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19605"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69836","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/69836"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EStudies have examined the psychological well-being and quality of life in patients with functional and inflammatory bowel conditions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the relationship between irritable bowel syndrome and psychological well-being?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Patients report poorer mental health than those with inflammatory bowel disease","Patients report better mental health than those with inflammatory bowel disease","Patients report identical mental health outcomes to those with inflammatory bowel disease","Patients report mental health outcomes similar to the general population","Patients report worse mental health during symptom flares only"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EResearch has consistently shown that \u003Cstrong\u003Epatients with irritable bowel syndrome report poorer mental health than those with inflammatory bowel disease\u003C/strong\u003E, despite IBD being generally considered a more severe condition. This highlights the significant psychological burden of functional gastrointestinal disorders.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBetter mental health outcomes\u003C/strong\u003E are not seen in IBS compared to IBD. The notion that patients have \u003Cstrong\u003Eidentical mental health outcomes\u003C/strong\u003E to IBD is incorrect. IBS patients do not have \u003Cstrong\u003Emental health outcomes similar to the general population\u003C/strong\u003E - they report significantly worse outcomes. While \u003Cstrong\u003Emental health may worsen during symptom flares\u003C/strong\u003E, the psychological impact of IBS persists even during periods of minimal symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Irritable bowel syndrome (IBS) patients report significantly poorer mental health outcomes compared to inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) patients.","The psychological impact of IBS is substantial despite its non-inflammatory nature."],"references":["Ford AC, Sperber AD, Corsetti M, Camilleri M. Irritable bowel syndrome. Lancet. 2020 Nov 21;396(10263):1675-1688. doi: 10.1016/S0140-6736(20)31548-8. Epub 2020 Oct 10. PMID: 33049223.","Camilleri M. Diagnosis and Treatment of Irritable Bowel Syndrome: A Review. JAMA. 2021 Mar 2;325(9):865-877. doi: 10.1001/jama.2020.22532. Erratum in: JAMA. 2021 Apr 20;325(15):1568. doi: 10.1001/jama.2021.4833. PMID: 33651094.","Patel N, Shackelford KB. Irritable Bowel Syndrome. [Updated 2022 Oct 30]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534810/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55292"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15386"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55292","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55292"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-12T20:17:39+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-12T20:20:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8077"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69836"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null